      "side": 1,
      "message": "Glad you asked this question :)  All SkParse methods are set up to match/consume part of the input, so I was assuming we want the same here.  E.g. \"blue foo bar\" would match blue and return a ptr to \" foo bar\", so strcmp wouldn\u0027t work.\n\nBut I just realized that\u0027s not what the old (or new) FindNamedColor impl is doing, and it would be pretty tricky to support for colors with common prefixes (\"blue\" vs. \"blueviolet\" - if we search for the latter, the former is also a valid partial match).\n\nSo I guess it makes sense to stick to the full-match behavior (I don\u0027t think SVG cares either way because color attributes are self-contained strings).\n\nSwitched to strcmp.",
      "parentUuid": "a29fae54_01cc7dc1",
      "revId": "2f1d54aaae204ec0b1aed52b8328252b5c3d6e06",
